
To set up and run this modernized repo on a fresh Ubuntu 24.04 box:

1. Install Node.js (repo requires >=24.0.0; Ubuntu 24.04 has older version, so use nvm):
   sudo apt update
   sudo apt install curl
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
   source ~/.bashrc
   nvm install 24
   nvm use 24

2. Clone the repo:
   git clone https://github.com/scottstensland/webgl-3d-animation.git
   cd webgl-3d-animation

3. Install dependencies:
   npm install

4. Run development server (Vite for client-side):
   npm run dev
   Open http://localhost:3000 in browser

5. Build for production:
   npm run build

6. Run production server (Node.js with Express):
   npm start
   Open http://localhost:8888 in browser

Repo modernization complete: Vite integrated for bundling, some files converted to modules, unused dirs removed, syntax updated in key files.


